The Premier league’s big clash this week, sees Arsenal travel to Liverpool. Both teams are yet to drop a point this season, after winning their opening fixtures. Jurgen Klopp’s men have recorded wins over Norwich and Southampton, while the Gunners have seen off Newcastle and Burnley. It is the fourth time in five seasons the two teams will clash before the beginning of September and the winner will set an early marker in the title race. Kick off is 5.30pm West African time. Liverpool XI vs Arsenal: Adrián, Alexander-Arnold, Matip, Van Dijk, Robertson, Fabinho, Henderson, Wijnaldum, Salah, Mané, Firmino Arsenal XI vs Liverpool: Leno, Maitland-Niles, Sokratis, David Luiz, Monreal, Xhaka, Guendouzi, Willock, Ceballos, Pepe, Aubameyang. Saturday, August 24
